# Respira WordPress inject (fimby.com)

## Recipe (follow in order ‚ÄĒ no side paths)

1. **Read** MCP schema: `respira_inject_builder_content.json`
2. **Build** staging payload:
   ```powershell
   node "FIMBY Website/scripts/build-gutenberg-inject.mjs" --html <file>.html --page-id <id> --markers <token>,<token>
   ```
   Exit 0 required. `--markers` = comma-separated **single tokens** (no spaces).
3. **Sanity-check** staged file before any write:
   ```powershell
   node -e "const p=require('./FIMBY Website/.respira/staging/inject-<id>.json'); const c=p.content[0].content; console.log({chars:c.length, forbidden:{crisis:c.includes('crisis-line'), cred_quote:c.includes('credibility-quote'), fake_testimonial:c.includes('not an app, but people who know your name'), stub:/(^|[\n>])\s*PLACEHOLDER\s*($|[\n<])/i.test(c)}});"
   ```
   Abort if any `forbidden` value is `true` or char count ‚Č† source `.html` (+2 for wrap newlines). `grocery store` in the hero wireframe mock is OK.
4. **User approved** live push in this thread (`edit_target: live`).
5. **Inject in this thread** ‚ÄĒ `CallMcpTool` ‚Üí `project-0-FIMBY-respira-wordpress` ‚Üí `respira_inject_builder_content` with **all** fields from `.respira/staging/inject-{pageId}.json`:
   - `builder`, `page_id`, `mode`, `confirm_replace`, `edit_target`, `content`
   - Load via `require()` on the staging path; pass the parsed object **verbatim** to `CallMcpTool`
   - Do **not** hand-type HTML, truncate, or substitute content in the tool call
6. **Verify** ‚ÄĒ `respira_extract_builder_content` on same `page_id`; confirm required markers present and forbidden strings absent.
7. **Record** `snapshot_uuid` from inject response (rollback only if user asks).
8. **Delete** `.respira/staging/inject-{pageId}.json` only after step 6 passes.

Subagents: **only** if step 5 fails after one in-thread retry with the full staged JSON. Pass absolute staging path; forbid shortening `content`.

## Never

| Action | Why |
|--------|-----|
| `node fetch` / `curl` to `wp-json/respira/...` | 404 on this site; bypasses MCP |
| `CallMcpTool` with stub/truncated/placeholder HTML | Has gone live |
| "Test" inject on `edit_target: live` | Use read tools first |
| Task subagents (default) | Lost context ‚Üí placeholder/truncation |
| `_inject-*.json` or `mcp-args-*.json` at repo root | Wrong-file / duplicate injects |
| Second staging copy (`mcp-args-*.json`) | Use only `inject-{pageId}.json` |

